SIMPLE: underwrite
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underwrite
<hw>Un`der*write"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Underwrote</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<mark>Obs</mark>. <conjf>Underwrit</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Underwritten</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>, <mark>Obs</mark>.
<conjf>Underwrit</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Underwriting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To write under
something else; to subscribe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What addition and change I have made I have here
<qex>underwritten</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Sanderson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To subscribe one's name to for insurance, especially
for marine insurance; to write one's name under, or set one's name to,
as a policy of insurance, for the purpose of becoming answerable for
loss or damage, on consideration of receiving a certain premium per
cent; <as>as, individuals, as well as companies, may <ex>underwrite</ex>
policies of insurance</as>.</def> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The broker who procures the insurance ought not, by
<qex>underwriting</qex> the policy, to deprive the parties of his
unbiased testimony.</q> <rj><qau>Marshall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underwrite</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Underwrite
<hw>Un`der*write"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To practice the business
of insuring; to take a risk of insurance on a vessel or the
like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underwriter</ent>⟦br⟧
